I've updated the plan based on your round-0 feedback. Please review the updated version at docs/plans/eden-phase-8a-wire-protocol.md. Key changes:

1. validate-terminal and validate/metrics are moved off the normative wire chapter and onto /_reference/ non-normative helper endpoints.
2. subscribe is now explicitly bound in 8a as a long-poll endpoint (GET /events/subscribe?cursor=N); polling companion remains. Not deferred.
3. InvalidPrecondition -> 409 (was 422).
4. Integrate-over-HTTP has a new 'Atomicity and composite-commit handling' subsection covering: (a) server-side same-value idempotency on POST /trials/{id}/integrate, (b) client-side read-back-before-compensate on indeterminate transport failures, (c) new IndeterminateIntegration error for unresolvable cases.
5. Same-value idempotency is also pushed into Store.integrate_trial itself so direct-store and wire-mediated paths share the contract.
6. New tests added: indeterminate-failure reconciliation, same-value idempotency, long-poll subscribe semantics.
7. 'Open questions' section is now 'Design decisions settled in round 0' capturing everything resolved.

Please check that (a) the atomicity story is now correct, (b) the subscribe binding is complete, (c) the normative/non-normative split is clean, and (d) there are no new issues introduced by the changes.
